      • MinMaxTestMainFürController

        public MinMaxTestMainFürController(J2R caller,
                                   double[][] VMatrix,
                                   java.lang.String[] rowNamesArray,
                                   java.lang.String[] colNamesArray,
                                   double[] u_lowArray,
                                   double[] u_highArray)
        The caller gets all the values which are needed to calculate the values vor Min and Max. A instance of MinMax is created to set the code for the calculations in R after that the runMinMax() method is called
        Parameters:
        caller - - an instance of the RCaller
        VMatrix - - the values of a VMatrix as double matrix
        rowNamesArray - - The row names of the VMatrix
        colNamesArray - - The col names of the VMatrix
        u_lowArray - - The SI low values of the Attributes as Array
        u_highArray - - The SI high values of the Attributes as Array

    • Method Detail

      • runMinMax

        public void runMinMax()
        In this method the code for the computations in R is transfered from the MinMax instance to the caller. After that the code is executed to get all the calculated values in the OutPutParser form R.
